<body>
Reports functions that have no RETURN statements.

<p>Example (Oracle):</p>

<pre>
<code>CREATE FUNCTION foo RETURN int AS
BEGIN
END;
</code></pre>

<p>The <code>foo</code> function must return the integer value but the function body returns nothing. To fix the error,
  add a RETURN statement (for example, <code>return 1;</code>).</p>

<pre><code>CREATE FUNCTION foo RETURN int AS
BEGIN
 RETURN 1;
END;</code></pre>
</body>
